content: Hi, I use touchstone to test our terminology server. There is one strange warnings on the simple expansion test extensional-case-3. The warning I got is "Minumum '/ValueSet/expansion/contains[47]/code' value of '248680001' could not be found in response." When I follow the url to http://implementation.e-imo.com/fhir/api/v1/ValueSet/extensional-case-3/$expand, I can see the code 248680001 is in the expansions.

@Yunwei Wang The validation for these tests is using the MinimumId assertion to compare the returned response from your server against a known, valid and staticly defined response message. The reporting level for these asserts is set to warning only to account any variances in the response message. I'll check on the comparison logic over the next couple of days. Thanks!
